Canadian Dollar Heads for Weekly Decline on Global Growth Slowdown Concern

-- B y   J o e   R a g a z z o
-- 
2011-08-05T15:14:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/canadian-dollar-declines-this-week-on-global-growth-slowdown-concern.html
Canada ’s dollar fell this week versus
its U.S. counterpart as concern the global economy is slowing
reduced investor demand for risk-associated assets.  The loonie fluctuated today as stocks fell and oil prices
dropped. Canada’s dollar gained earlier after reports showed the
nation and its largest trading partner added jobs last month.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
